org.hibernate.boot.model.relational

Interface MappedAuxiliaryDatabaseObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAuxiliaryDatabaseObject, SimpleAuxiliaryDatabaseObject

    public interface MappedAuxiliaryDatabaseObject
extends Serializable
    Auxiliary database objects (i.e., triggers, stored procedures, etc) defined in the mappings. Allows Hibernate to manage their lifecycle as part of creating/dropping the schema.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  MappedAuxiliaryDatabaseObject.Expandable
      Additional, optional interface for AuxiliaryDatabaseObject that want to allow expansion of allowable dialects via mapping.

      • beforeTablesOnCreation

        boolean beforeTablesOnCreation()
        Defines a simple precedence. Should creation of this auxiliary object happen beforeQuery creation of tables? If true, the auxiliary object creation will happen afterQuery any explicit schema creations but beforeQuery table/sequence creations; if false, the auxiliary object creation will happen afterQuery explicit schema creations and afterQuery table/sequence creations. This precedence is automatically inverted for dropping.
        Returns:
        true indicates this object should be created beforeQuery tables; false indicates it should be created afterQuery.
